> Starters, boilerplates and companion projects that extend or make it easier to work with Assemble. Some of these are from Assemble's core team, others from the community. "Thank you!" to all the creators of these projects! We really appreciate your support!


## Generators
### Yeoman

* [generator-assemble](https://github.com/hariadi/generator-assemble): Yeoman generator for Assemble. Authored by [@hariadi](https://github.com/hariadi).

### Grunt Init

* [grunt-init-assemble](https://github.com/assemble/grunt-init-assemble) Grunt init template for creating Assemble projects.
* [grunt-init-helper](https://github.com/assemble/grunt-init-helper) Grunt init template for creating [Handlebars helpers][helpers] for use with Assemble.

## Assemble Boilerplates

{{#draft}}* [andismith/site-boilerplate](https://github.com/andismith/site-boilerplate): A complete grunt site boilerplate{{/draft}}
* [hariadi/assemble-jekyll](https://github.com/hariadi/assemble-jekyll): Yeoman generator for Assemble that generate layouts, pages, partials, and markdown content for Jekyll static site.
* [assemble/boilerplate-site](https://github.com/assemble/boilerplate-site): Demonstrates how to use Assemble to build a site. Includes layouts, pages, partials, and markdown content.
* [assemble/boilerplate-sitemap](https://github.com/assemble/boilerplate-sitemap): Generate a sitemap with Assemble.
* [assemble/boilerplate-gist-blog](https://github.com/assemble/boilerplate-gist-blog): Assemble a blog from GitHub Gists.
* [assemble/boilerplate-markdown](https://github.com/assemble/boilerplate-markdown): Use Assemble to generate HTML pages from markdown content. Useful for wikis, gh-pages, documentation and blogs or sites with markdown posts
* [assemble/boilerplate-readme](https://github.com/assemble/boilerplate-readme): Use Assemble to generate a README, wiki pages, or other basic markdown documentation. This project features special helpers for maintaining readmes.

## Helpers

* [handlebars-helpers](https://github.com/assemble/handlebars-helpers): Library of 110+ handlebars helpers. This project is active and supported, we love contributors and appreciate watchers.
* [handlebars-helpers-examples](https://github.com/assemble/handlebars-helpers-examples): Dozens (maybe more than 100?) examples for using helpers with Assemble.

## Sublime Text

* [sublime-markdown-extended](https://github.com/jonschlinkert/sublime-markdown-extended): Sublime Text package that extends Soda's Monokai and the default markdown styles with additional syntax highlighting for [YAML Front Matter](http://assemble.io/docs/YAML-front-matter.html), GitHub Flavored Markdown (GFM) and language-specific syntax highlighting inside [GFM "fenced" code blocks](https://help.github.com/articles/github-flavored-markdown#syntax-highlighting)

